urs off those loathsome giants; once, i think i picked 40pp total off of one (just when i thought all the plat was gone, he gives up a few more =D) yes, a sow is required, but a few plat donation is well worth the cause!  The wait, however does suck (once said 40+ guys kill the poor ol sand giant) but funding for new gear is in the works!<br>
Brothers and sisters, if you havent tried this yet, you are soo missing out!<br>
<br>
ps.<br>
<br>
while waiting, i even picked those fubjhm gypsies that would never sell to me (well now they do, now that sneak is high enough and i dont have to spend an hour attempting to get sneak to succeed like i did when i was younger) <br>
&quot;yes, once i clean you out, I will go back to the rock i crawled out under, mutherbiaatch!&quot;<br>
<br>
It Is Soo Great To be A Rogue! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoaksheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oaksheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 10:56:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> Your the reason I quit EQ. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umegillagerilla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Megilla Gerilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 12:10:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> i hope you get caught and killed, and your body with all the stolen plat falls under the world or something<br>
<br>
have a nice day <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 12:15:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> He's a rogue, what's wrong with him pickpocketing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unruter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nruter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 12:35:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> I wont say that I never pickpocket, had to raise the skill for epic of course.<br>
<br>
I had never been able to figure out how pickpocketing would be more efficient then just hunting and getting loot at these levels.  I also find the game much more enjoyable when hunting and exploring new places with friends.<br>
<br>
Well to each his/her own, it is after all just a game.<br>
<br>
Nruter<br>
lil Blackguard<br>
Quellious-Ring Warden<br>
<br>
(edit was correcting a typo) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unruter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nruter</A> at: 9/18/01 12:35:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 12:53:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> Giants all over are good for that sorta thing-though I have heard stories of rogues that pickpocket entire _dungeons_ for fun and practice.<br>
 <br>
I'd love to see the rogue that manages to pickpocket the Hole. :P<br>
 <br>
-Morgrist,Innoruuk server.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Momus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/01 11:27:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> I don't mind rogues PPing a mob that isn't theirs, as long as they don't mind me charming their mobs just as it is about to die. I mean, that's a class skill of Enchanters, isn't it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufortunadofuerte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fortunado Fuerte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/01 5:54:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> voice your comments elsewhere then. This is a rogue board and you really shouldn't be criticizing rogues on it.<br>
<br>
Pick pocket doesn't prevent you from gaining exp. Besides, for all you know that giant might have only had silver and copper to begin with. Do rogues bitch that they can't solo a giant like necros and druids can? No, cause we have alternative ways of getting the money from them. You might as well go over to the Druid's Glade and yell at them because they can track down rare spawns before you have a chance to find them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Momus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/01 11:07:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> I didn't intend to insult rogues on their home turf. I have been the benefactor of many a PP, mainly spells. I just think that PPing a mob that someone else is valiantly ( or easily) killing, seems pretty trecherous. It's not like hitting something for faction, or practicing 2HB.<br>
<br>
Forgive me for not sharing your complete neutrality with regards to Alignment as it pertains to playing the game. I generally play a neutral good sort of chanter. <br>
<br>
Differing views don't hurt us, but I suppose I chose the wrong forum for such nonsense.<br>
<br>
Lantris<br>
Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unobelnovember.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nobel November</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 1:09:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm</span><hr size=1> PPing someone elses MOB is the same as KSing.<br>
<br>
Nobel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhubbestubbe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HubbeStubbe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 10:52:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> No its not the same as KSing.. How-ever.. He never said he pick pocketed engaged mobs.. He is engaging them so they belong to him. Only way it might effect someone is if someone kills it after he zones to clear aggro... <br>
<br>
Tell me again how this is really bad?<br>
<br>
Esp. since a plat pool &quot;regens&quot; after a while. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utallastaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tallas Taranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 11:15:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> server gm once told me that pick pocketing a mob comes from a different loot table for cash,   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalynntaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalynn Taranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 11:27:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> Heh - I PP mobs all the time - but only the ones my group is fighting.  I always give any cash gems to a cleric because I know they need them.  Sometimes I bring my own periodots and when I do that then I don't give them any gems, hehe.<br>
<br>
Most clerics know I am giving them PP gems and they are very thankful for it - never did they complain about that.  And if I was in a really kickass group, I will put up any good gems I PP (diamonds, BD, etc) up for lotto along with the rest of the loot.  If however, they were all jerks I keep it.  The way I see it it's my payment for putting up with them =) <br>
<br>
I don't see a problem with PP so long as its not overdone.  <br>
<br>
In terms of the loot table - it did used to come from a different pool but they changed that.  Now when we PP we take cash and loot from the actual mob =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utallastaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tallas Taranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 11:31:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> damn my wifey is so smart <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    thats why i loves her <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
/hugs baby <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalynntaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalynn Taranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 11:31:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> <3 Tallas =)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 12:05:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> Tallas - please read the FAQ in the Training Studio.  PP Loot does NOT NOT NOT (get that?) come from a different pool.  It used to, but not for a long time.  Don't want to sound harsh, but that myth must be killed.<br>
<br>
PPing an engaged mob is not KSing, but it is *very* tacky and a good way to get kept out of groups with a spoiled rep.  An UNENGAGED mob, however, *should* be picked clean! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Why should I care if some caster pulls the mob after I've emptied it.  It encourages re-spawn and I'm glad for that.  I've gone to RM a couple of times to do a little picking but I've not 'engaged' the mob and don't feel entitled to squawk if someone wants to rob it of its xp-value.<br>
<br>
I also agree, to a large extent, with Fortunado.  Solo, there are very few *viable* means for a rogue to make monies.  SoW potions sell to *anybody* for 100/10.  Rezzes maybe 50-100.  Ports/TLs, usually 10-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 200</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->pp.  <br>
How much do non-stacking poisons sell for?  And to whom?  Nooooobody. :/<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=crowley>Crowley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 12:43:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> This is just one of those subjects better kept silent... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufalonvanyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falon Vanyer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 8:17:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> Sorry to drag this old subject up again, but you'd better confirm with a GM if this not considered KS'ing.<br>
<br>
I know someone who was given an official warning on their account by a GM for tagging mobs for faction that another group was killing. The GM said that it was considered kill stealing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 8:25:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> I believe the &quot;KS&quot; issue is a grayer one, on a server-by-server basis.  I've heard some GMs hold the KS attitude, while others just shrug it off so long as you're not taking the xp from the other player. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqwillian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwillian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 10:55:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mad Cash Disease!</span><hr size=1> An UNengaged MoB = Fair Game<br>
<br>
Period<br>
<br>
End of conversation<br>
<br>
